SIMPLE: unchild
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unchild
<hw>Un*child"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>child</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To bereave of children; to make childless.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make unlike a child; to divest of the
characteristics of a child.</def> <rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unchristen</ent>⟦br⟧
